Key Match Events: Pakistan won by 7 wickets with 5 balls remaining.
Haris Rauf got out with two runs to get, but Pakistan reached the World Cup final.
Pakistan got a wicket on the third ball and kept New Zealand to 38 for 2 in the powerplay.
The 58-run third wicket stand between Kane Williamson and Daryl Mitchell was New Zealand's strongest partnership.
Pakistan allowed just 53 runs off the last six overs of New Zealand's innings.
Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan put on 105 runs for the first wicket.
Trent Boult took the wicket of Babar Azam.
Shaheen Afridi dismissed Finn Allen on the third ball of the match.
Shaheen Afridi dismissed Kane Williamson for 46 off 42 balls.
Shadab Khan's direct hit run-out of Devon Conway.
Pre-Game Insights: New Zealand won the toss and chose to bat first.
Spinners have a substantially better economy rate at the SCG this World Cup.
Both teams were unchanged from their previous matches.
Pakistan have a history of performing well in knockout stages of tournaments.
Post-Match Reflections: Pakistan were better with the bat, ball, and fielding compared to New Zealand.
Pakistan's journey to the semi-finals was unexpected as they had little hope of making it as recently as Sunday morning.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Sydney Cricket Ground.
There was a significant presence of Pakistan supporters in the stands.
